OL,7,FShe says she remembers being driven in
OL,8,Fdifferent cars, sometimes in pyjamas,
OL,9,Fto flats which were full of men who
OL,10,Fwould supply her and her friend with
OL,11,Falcohol and drugs.
OL,13,F"Obviously, at the time, you didn't
OL,14,Frealise what was happening. You just
OL,15,Fthink it's a place to get drunk. It's
OL,16,Fonly when you get older you realise
OL,17,Fthat was pure wrong.
